name: Education - Mammograms
description:
Introduction:

With the advancement of new technologies in the field of Radiology, the possible use of these for teaching should be explored, in order to complement the traditional study and testing that occur throughout the training of a Radiologist.
Using the MD.ai platform, residents have the possibility to test their knowledge in real exams, anonymized, with various degrees of difficulty and proven findings, to ensure an adequate testing environment.

Objectives:
- Create a project to test residents' skills in mammogram analysis and interpretation.
- Possible subdivision of cases depending on the subjects to be tested, with suggested references for each theme.
- Comparison with the "ground-truth" annotations provided by subspecialty trained radiologists and provided labels in open-source datasets.

Subjects to test:
- BI-RADS Findings Annotation: Breast composition classes, Mass, Architectural Distortion, Calcifications (with subclassification into typically benign, amorphous, course heterogeneous, fine pleomorphic and fine linear/fine linear branching)
- Global BI-RADS classification


Datasets:
https://wiki.cancerimagingarchive.net/display/Public/CBIS-DDSM

Suggested References:
Laszlo Tabar, Peter B. Dean, Tibor Tot - Teaching Atlas of Mammography (2011, Thieme)
Debra M. Ikeda, Kanae K. Miyake MD - Breast Imaging The Requisites 3rd Edition (2017, Elsevier)

To learn how to annotate on MD.ai, please visit https://docs.md.ai
For other inquiries, please contact quan@md.ai
